From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 19:30:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] DO NOT SUBMIT: net: dsa: mxl862xx: expose legacy PCS caps

The legacy SYS_MISC_SFP_SET-based PCS fallback is selected for firmware
versions older than 1.0.84, but phylink_get_caps() still returned an
empty supported_interfaces bitmap for SerDes ports on those firmware
versions.

That makes phylink reject the CPU port before the legacy PCS fallback can
be used. Expose the interface modes handled by mxl862xx_legacy_pcs_config()
for the slot-0 SerDes ports used by the legacy API.

This commit is for downstream use only and must not be submitted upstream.
Future upstream work should replace this with the mainline-supported old
firmware compatibility model, if one lands.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@openai.com>
---
 drivers/net/dsa/mxl862xx/mxl862xx-phylink.c | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/dsa/mxl862xx/mxl862xx-phylink.c
+++ b/drivers/net/dsa/mxl862xx/mxl862xx-phylink.c
@@ -22,8 +22,15 @@ void mxl862xx_phylink_get_caps(struct ds
 		break;
 	case 9:
 	case 13:
-		if (!MXL862XX_FW_VER_MIN(priv, 1, 0, 84))
+		if (!MXL862XX_FW_VER_MIN(priv, 1, 0, 84)) {
+			__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_SGMII, config->supported_interfaces);
+			__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_1000BASEX, config->supported_interfaces);
+			__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_2500BASEX, config->supported_interfaces);
+			__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_10GBASER, config->supported_interfaces);
+			__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_USXGMII, config->supported_interfaces);
 			break;
+		}
+
 		__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_SGMII, config->supported_interfaces);
 		__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_1000BASEX, config->supported_interfaces);
 		__set_bit(PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_2500BASEX, config->supported_interfaces);
